<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-08-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-08-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="144" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d144">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.3731/906: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-08-15">August 15, 1934</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your 393, August 15, 9 a.m. Department concurs in your opinion that
                            immediate reduction of consular fee advisable and believes it should be
                            insisted upon.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>